                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 73rb: This Four Gospel book is of ras Sǝbḥat who donated it to (the church of) St. John (of) Däbrä Maʿḍo, so that it might be a guide for him to the Kingdom of Heaven; and his baptismal name is Kidanä Maryam, and the name of his mother is Wälättä Sǝllase, and the name(s) of his children are Gäbrä Ḥǝywät, Wäldä Gäbrǝʾel, ʾArʾaya Śǝllase. Oh God of John, protect his life, and forgive his sins, and subdue [fol. 73va] his enemy to the feet of your servant Kidanä Maryam, and protect all the people of his house from a plague of flesh and soul. And anyone who stole (the book) and erased (what is written in it), be excommunicated through the authority of Peter and Paul.  This Four Gospel book is of ras Sǝbḥat who bought it with his own money.   </q>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Stamp of ras Sǝbḥat ʾArägawi: fols. 2r, 4r, 19r, 73v, 109r, 161r. &#xD;
